# ScriptoNet

ScriptoNet is a multi-task transformer-based framework for detecting, classifying, and quantifying therapeutic mechanisms in literary fiction.

---

## 📌 Problem Statement
This project analyzes therapeutic mechanisms in literary passages using NLP models.

---

## 🧠 Model Architecture
- RoBERTa encoder
- BiLSTM layer
- 3 output heads:
  - Therapeutic event detection
  - Mechanism classification (5 classes)
  - Intensity regression

---

## 📊 Tasks
1. Binary classification (Therapeutic event detection)
2. Five-class mechanism classification
3. Intensity prediction (1–5 scale)

---

## 📁 Dataset
McEwan Therapeutic Corpus (expert annotated literary passages)

